<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1910-04-03T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1910-04-03T00:00:00-05:00" n="445" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d445">
                        <head><hi rend="italic">Minister <persName type="from">Fox</persName> to the
                                    <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>.</hi></head>
                        <opener><seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg></opener>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">American Legation</hi>,<lb/><hi rend="italic">Quito</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1910-04-03"><hi rend="italic">April 3,
                                1910</hi></date>.</dateline></opener>
                        <p>Referring to my April 1, the following have been appointed as special
                            delegates by the Government of Ecuador to treat with those appointed by
                            Peru in direct settlement of the boundary question: Luis Felipe Carbo,
                            Felicisimo Lopez, and Clemente Ponce.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Fox.</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>